    "oled_displays_p2": "OLED stuck pixels can sometimes respond to pixel fixer stimulation, though results vary more than LCD displays. Some users report better success rates with OLED than LCD, while others report worse results. The self-emissive nature of OLEDs means stuck pixels are more visible and more problematic for display quality. OLED dead pixels are essentially permanent and cannot be repaired without panel replacement.",
    "dead_pixel_faq_title": "Frequently Asked Questions",
    "dead_pixel_faq_q1": "Can software really repair a dead pixel?",
