    "monitor_gaming_360hz_intro": "360Hz monitors represent the pinnacle of competitive gaming displays. These tests verify your 360Hz display is performing at its peak. Check for dead pixels and color accuracy.",
    "monitor_professional": "Professional Monitor Test",
    "monitor_professional_title": "Professional Monitor Test - Color-Accurate Display Verification",
    "monitor_professional_description": "Test professional-grade monitors for color-critical work. Verify color accuracy, dead pixels, and reference performance.",
    "monitor_professional_intro": "Professional monitors are engineered for color accuracy and reliability. These tests verify your professional display is maintaining calibration and consistency. Perfect for designers, photographers, and video editors.",
    "monitor_photo_editing": "Photo Editing Monitor Test",
    "monitor_photo_editing_title": "Photo Editing Monitor Test - Color Accuracy Verification",
    "monitor_photo_editing_description": "Complete photo editing monitor testing. Verify color accuracy, dead pixels, and photography display performance.",
    "monitor_photo_editing_intro": "Photo editing monitors are built for color-accurate image work. These tests verify your photo editing display is delivering the color precision photographers and editors demand. Check for dead pixels and color uniformity.",
    "monitor_video_editing": "Video Editing Monitor Test",
    "monitor_video_editing_title": "Video Editing Monitor Test - Color Grading Display Verification",
    "monitor_video_editing_description": "Test video editing and color grading monitors. Verify color accuracy, dead pixels, and 4K editing performance.",
    "monitor_video_editing_intro": "Video editing monitors deliver accurate color reproduction for grading and editing work. These tests verify your video editing display is delivering color precision and consistency. Ideal for colorists and video professionals.",
    "monitor_faq_1_q": "How do I know if my monitor has dead pixels?",
    "monitor_faq_1_a": "Use our color screen tests (red, blue, green, white) to spot dead pixels. Dead pixels appear as small dots that don't match the color being displayed. They're easiest to see on solid color backgrounds.",
    "monitor_faq_2_q": "What's the difference between dead pixels and stuck pixels?",
    "monitor_faq_2_a": "Dead pixels are always off (black dots), while stuck pixels are always on (bright spots). Both are defects. Some stuck pixels can be revived with special software, but dead pixels are permanent.",
    "monitor_faq_3_q": "How accurate are these monitor tests?",
    "monitor_faq_3_a": "Our tests use the same methods professional technicians use for monitor quality control. They reveal the same defects you'd find in any professional display testing environment.",
    "monitor_tests": "Test Your Monitor",
    "related_monitor_tests": "Test Other Monitor Brands",
    "iphone_test": "iPhone Screen Test",
    "iphone_test_title": "iPhone Screen Test - Check Display Quality",
    "iphone_test_description": "Complete iPhone screen testing. Check for dead pixels, color accuracy, brightness, and overall display quality with professional resources.",
    "iphone_test_intro": "Your iPhone display is critical to your daily experience. Our professional testing resources help you verify your screen is performing perfectly. Whether you're checking a new iPhone, diagnosing a problem, or verifying a refurbished device, these tests reveal exactly what you're working with.",
    "iphone_faq_1_q": "Can these tests detect pixel-level damage on iPhones?",
    "iphone_faq_1_a": "Yes. By displaying solid colors and gradients, these tests reveal dead pixels, stuck pixels, and color shifts at the pixel level. Any defects become immediately visible.",
    "iphone_faq_2_q": "Do these tests work on all iPhone models?",
    "iphone_faq_2_a": "Yes! These tests work on every iPhone with a modern browser, from older models to the latest Pro Max. The screen size doesn't matter - defects show up the same way.",
    "macbook_test": "MacBook Screen Test",
    "macbook_test_title": "MacBook Screen Test - Verify Display Quality",
    "macbook_test_description": "Professional MacBook display testing. Check Retina screen quality, color accuracy, dead pixels, and brightness uniformity.",
    "macbook_test_intro": "MacBook displays are among the best in the industry. But even premium screens can have defects. These professional tests help you verify your MacBook display is performing perfectly. Test for dead pixels, color accuracy, and brightness consistency across the entire Retina display.",
    "macbook_faq_1_q": "How do I test my MacBook Retina display?",
    "macbook_faq_1_a": "Simply load each test fullscreen on your MacBook. The pure color displays will immediately reveal any dead pixels or color inconsistencies. The contrast and brightness tests verify uniformity.",
    "macbook_faq_2_q": "Are MacBook displays really more durable than other laptops?",
    "macbook_faq_2_a": "MacBook displays are excellent quality, but they can still develop defects. These tests help you catch issues early, whether you're verifying a new device or troubleshooting an existing one.",
    "oled_tv_test": "OLED TV Test",
    "oled_tv_test_title": "OLED TV Test - Professional Display Testing",
    "oled_tv_test_description": "Complete OLED TV testing. Check for burn-in risk, color accuracy, black levels, and overall OLED panel quality.",
    "oled_tv_test_intro": "OLED TVs deliver stunning picture quality with perfect blacks and infinite contrast. But OLED panels are susceptible to burn-in and pixel issues. These professional tests verify your OLED TV is working optimally and reveal any pixel defects. Essential for verifying new OLED purchases and testing for burn-in patterns.",
    "oled_tv_faq_1_q": "Can your tests detect OLED burn-in?",
    "oled_tv_faq_1_a": "Yes. Burn-in appears as image persistence or discoloration. By using solid colors and patterns, our tests can reveal stuck pixels and early signs of burn-in damage.",
    "oled_tv_faq_2_q": "What causes OLED burn-in?",
    "oled_tv_faq_2_a": "Burn-in happens when static images stay on the screen too long, causing organic pixels to degrade permanently. It's more common with OLED than LED/LCD because the pixels emit their own light.",
    "gaming_monitor_test": "Gaming Monitor Test",
    "gaming_monitor_test_title": "Gaming Monitor Test - 144Hz+ Display Quality Check",
    "gaming_monitor_test_description": "Professional gaming monitor testing. Verify 144Hz+ refresh rate, color accuracy, response time, and display quality for competitive gaming.",
    "gaming_monitor_test_intro": "Gaming monitors demand peak performance. Whether you're using 144Hz, 165Hz, 240Hz, or even 360Hz displays, these professional tests verify your gaming monitor is delivering. Check for dead pixels, color accuracy, and overall display quality that impacts competitive gaming performance.",
    "gaming_monitor_faq_1_q": "How do I verify my gaming monitor's refresh rate?",
    "gaming_monitor_faq_1_a": "Our color and contrast tests help verify smooth rendering and proper color display at high refresh rates. Consistent performance across all tests indicates proper refresh rate function.",
    "gaming_monitor_faq_2_q": "Why is color accuracy important for gaming?",
    "gaming_monitor_faq_2_a": "Accurate colors give you visibility advantages in competitive games. You'll spot enemies more easily and get better color-based cues. Professional gamers prioritize color accuracy alongside refresh rate.",
